                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.12/31a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="25" xml:id="d487fn25">Sent also to consular officers at
                        Ciudad Juarez; Matamoros; Mazatlan; Monterey; Mexico, D.F.; Piedras Negras;
                        and Vera Cruz.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-05T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Report your opinion as to advisability of resuming extradition proceedings with
                    Mexican Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
